# Unit Test Coverage

- Maintain at least 80% unit test coverage for the project.
- When adding or changing behavior, add or update focused unit tests so coverage stays at or above 80%.
- If coverage tooling is present, run the appropriate coverage command before considering changes complete.
- If coverage cannot be verified locally, call that out clearly and explain what still needs to be checked.
